S3 Storage classes:
1. S3 standard General Purpose
High durability, no loss of data
Use cases: Big DATA analytics, monile & gaming apps.

2. S3 Standard - Infrequent Access (IA)
it is for less frequently accessed data, low cost.
Use cases: As a data store for disaster recovery, backups.

3. S3 One Zone - Infrequent Access (IA)
Same as IA but data is stored in a single AZ.
Use cases: secondary backups, store data which can recreate.

4. S3 Intelligent Tiering
Automatically moves objects b/w two access tires(S3 IA and S3 general purpose) based on changing patterns.

5. Amazon Glacier.
Low cost, data retained for longer term.
Each item in Glacier is called archive, archives stored in vaults not in buckets.
3-retrival options:
expedite(1-5 min)
standard(3to5 hours)
bulk(5-12hours)
Min storage duration 90 days.

6. Amazon Glacier  Deep Archive- for long term storage- cheaper:
standard(12 hours)
bulk(48 hours)
Min storage duration 180 days
